From: hermes-agent <kernel@oneplus-nord-ce5>
Date: Mon, 8 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 0005] mm/memcontrol: replay android_vh_mem_cgroup_alloc for hybridswap backlog

The OPLUS hybridswap vendor module (oplus_bsp_hybridswap_zram.ko) is a
self-contained zram replacement loaded from vendor_dlkm in second stage,
after init has already created dozens of memory cgroups. It attaches its
per-memcg object table from inside the android_vh_mem_cgroup_alloc vendor
hook, which only fires on *new* memcg allocation, so every memcg that
already existed at insmod time keeps a NULL oem_data table and hybridswap
floods dmesg with "table = 0000000000000000 / idx = -22 invalid".

Fix: a late_initcall delayed work waits (static-key poll) for the vendor
probe to register, then walks every live memcg via mem_cgroup_iter() and
replays the alloc hook. The vendor mem_cgroup_alloc_hook early-returns when
android_oem_data1[0] is already set (verified by disassembly: ldr x8,[x1,
0x8e0]; cbnz x8), so the replay is idempotent. KMI-safe: no new exported
symbol, reuses the existing android_vh_mem_cgroup_alloc tracepoint.

Signed-off-by: hermes-agent <kernel@oneplus-nord-ce5>
---
diff --git a/mm/memcontrol.c b/mm/memcontrol.c
--- a/mm/memcontrol.c
+++ b/mm/memcontrol.c
@@ -5716,6 +5716,59 @@
 	lru_gen_release_memcg(memcg);
 }
 
+/*
+ * OPLUS hybridswap replay: the vendor hybridswap module (loaded from
+ * vendor_dlkm, i.e. well after init has already created dozens of memory
+ * cgroups) attaches its per-memcg object table inside
+ * android_vh_mem_cgroup_alloc. Because that probe only fires when a *new*
+ * memcg is allocated, every memcg that already existed when the module was
+ * inserted is left with a NULL table (android_oem_data1[0] == 0), which is
+ * exactly the "table = 0000000000000000 / idx = -22 invalid" flood seen in
+ * HYB_ZRAM logs.
+ *
+ * Fix: once the vendor probe is registered, walk every live memcg and replay
+ * the alloc hook on it. The vendor probe is idempotent -- it bails out early
+ * for any memcg whose oem_data slot is already populated -- so replaying is
+ * safe both for the backlog and for any memcg the live hook already handled.
+ */
+static void memcg_hybridswap_replay_work(struct work_struct *work);
+static DECLARE_DELAYED_WORK(memcg_hybridswap_replay_dwork,
+			    memcg_hybridswap_replay_work);
+static unsigned int memcg_hybridswap_replay_tries;
+
+/* poll every 200ms, give up after ~240s of uptime if no module ever loads */
+#define MEMCG_HYBRIDSWAP_REPLAY_INTERVAL_MS	200
+#define MEMCG_HYBRIDSWAP_REPLAY_MAX_TRIES	1200
+
+static void memcg_hybridswap_replay_work(struct work_struct *work)
+{
+	struct mem_cgroup *memcg;
+
+	if (!trace_android_vh_mem_cgroup_alloc_enabled()) {
+		if (++memcg_hybridswap_replay_tries <
+		    MEMCG_HYBRIDSWAP_REPLAY_MAX_TRIES)
+			schedule_delayed_work(&memcg_hybridswap_replay_dwork,
+				msecs_to_jiffies(
+					MEMCG_HYBRIDSWAP_REPLAY_INTERVAL_MS));
+		return;
+	}
+
+	for (memcg = mem_cgroup_iter(NULL, NULL, NULL); memcg;
+	     memcg = mem_cgroup_iter(NULL, memcg, NULL))
+		trace_android_vh_mem_cgroup_alloc(memcg);
+}
+
+static int __init memcg_hybridswap_replay_init(void)
+{
+	if (mem_cgroup_disabled())
+		return 0;
+
+	schedule_delayed_work(&memcg_hybridswap_replay_dwork,
+		msecs_to_jiffies(MEMCG_HYBRIDSWAP_REPLAY_INTERVAL_MS));
+	return 0;
+}
+late_initcall(memcg_hybridswap_replay_init);
+
 static void mem_cgroup_css_free(struct cgroup_subsys_state *css)
 {
 	struct mem_cgroup *memcg = mem_cgroup_from_css(css);
